        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p
                rend="The following 5 lines printed as a letterhead, April 19th inserted on dotted line."/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Office Assistant Quartermaster,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Bureau Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned
                    Lands</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>STATE OF LOUISIANA</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>No. 32 Carondelet St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>April 19th 1866</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your favor under date <date>12</date> Inst. is before<lb/> me, &amp;
                felt some what <sic>supprised</sic> to find you have<lb/> sent the Books by Express
                without my ordering<lb/> them, If you will <sic>refere</sic> to my letter on
                the<lb/> subject you will find I only asked if you Could<lb/> Supply me with a set
                of the same as I had of<lb/> you some time ago. &amp; what would be the price<lb/>
                if sent by the Express. I called at the express office<lb/> &amp; found the parcel
                but in my asking to open it<lb/> the refused until I paid $73.40<lb/>100 which I
                refused<lb/> to do until I heard from you on the subject.<lb/> You may remember I
                only paid you $3<add>?</add> in paper &amp; I had them bound in Red Morocco &amp;
                Gold with<lb/> my name which cost $12 in <placeName>New York</placeName> making them
                to<lb/> cost $48 only. Yet I suppose as labour is now<lb/> higher &amp; things
                altered I must submit to a higher<lb/> price. I am sorry you are so
                    <sic>premiture</sic> in<lb/> sending them until they were ordered. I find</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>you charge $25 for five Vol &amp; $37 for seven<lb/> why a <sic>diffeer</sic> of $2
                on the Seven? I want<lb/> the Books and will have no objections<lb/> to pay the part
                of the Bill, say $68.40<lb/>100 but<lb/> I will not pay one Cent more, as I
                consider<lb/> that amount quite enough,= you will therefore<lb/> have to send a note
                enclosed in my letter<lb/> to the Express office directing them to allow me to
                inspect the Books before I pay<lb/> the amount and if they are to orders<lb/> of my
                    memorandum<add>?</add> say Bound in <sic>Morrocco</sic><lb/> &amp; Gold Gilt
                Edges and names on the covers<lb/> I will pay the amnt. but I shall never
                consent<lb/> to pay such exorbitant charges= if you were<lb/> not so
                    <sic>premiture</sic> I intended to have got them<lb/> sent to <placeName>New
                    York</placeName> to a friend who would have brought them free of charge. Besides
                you<lb/> have not stated what books you sent &amp;<lb/> if all my memorandum calls
                for, are sent,<lb/> please look on my Memorandum as I named<lb/> all the Books I
                wanted, times are very<lb/> hard and you must <add>not</add> blame me if I seek<lb/>
                to get what I want, please let me hear from<lb/> you <sic>imediately</sic> as I wish
                to have this matter<lb/> closed one way or the other, as it is no use<lb/> having
                the books laying at the Express office.<lb/> Remember, send the letter to allow me
                to look at them<lb/> &amp; I am to pay <hi rend="underline">only</hi> the nett amnt
                of $68.40<lb/> &amp; no more for <sic>chages</sic>; if they are to my
                <add>?</add><lb/> trusting to hear from you <sic>imediately</sic> I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Yours <sic>Respetfully</sic></p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">D. Carvalho</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
